title: Ask HN: What Happened to Ceylon Language?
text: I was reading a post about yet another language on HN's front page when I was reminded of Ceylon language which some years back was being promoted as an alternative to Java. I remember seeing it frequently those years but then I stopped following. Now I searched for it and it looks abandoned? The latest news I can find is that it's been donated to Eclipse foundation. What happened?
